de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order

Class MeasurementOrder

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order.MeasurementOrder

  • public class MeasurementOrder
extends Object
    The measurement order specifies what to measure for a MeasurementTool. The idea behind this is, that MeasurementTools don't depend on the Blackboard and don't need to know about it's structure.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MeasurementOrder

        public MeasurementOrder(Set<CodeSection> parameterValueSections,
                        Set<CodeSection> resourceDemandSections,
                        Set<CodeSection> executionSections,
                        ProjectInformation projectInformation,
                        ParameterCharacteriser parameterCharacteriser)
        Create a measurement order for MeasurementTools.
        Parameters:
        parameterValueSections - The code sections where parameters need to be characterised. Must not be null. May not contain null elements.
        resourceDemandSections - The code sections, where all resource demands need to be captured. Must not be null. May not contain null elements.
        executionSections - The code sections, where an MeasurementEvent should be created each time it gets executed. Must not be null. May not contain null elements.
        projectInformation - The measured project’s configuration. Must not be null.
        parameterCharacteriser - The parameter characteriser, that all measurement tools must use for parameter characterisation. Must not be null.
